Program: Great Lives
Title: Julia Ward-Howe
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gj8m4
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 5 Sep 2006
Matthew Parris is joined by Elaine Showalter to discuss the 19th-century American writer Julia Ward-Howe. Best known as the author of the Battle Hymn of the Republic, she was a feminist, pacifist and a great lost poet. Proffessor Gary Williams joins the debate.